g.text: Presentation layer is deﬁned by MVP pattern.
Presenter is a gateway between data store
layer and domain layer. Here you can have any
logic related to data ﬂow between those
Presentation logic should contain any logic
related to data ﬂow which can be for example
calling multiple use cases and then updating data
Generally you should map domain model to
presentation as structure may differ depending
on the screen. But sometimes you can use domain
model when you see that both structures are
exactly the same and won't change in a future.
Data store here allows to update
data, update data on data source side
etc. We can also get data from store
Domain is represented by Use Case, Interactor
or Scenario patterns, and it's a entry point to
data source. It contains business logic for a
speciﬁc user action. We can inject to presenter
